Fergo Aisa, Portugal Telecom: Iberian Equity Market Preview

-- B y   C h a r l e s   P e n t y
-- 
2011-05-26T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/fergo-aisa-portugal-telecom-iberian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  rose 1 percent to 10,217.40.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  rose 0.9 percent to 7,665.53.  Spanish stocks:  Fergo Aisa SA (AISA SM): The real estate company said in a
filing it hoped to reach an accord soon on a debt dispute with
CatalunyaCaixa, a bank. In the meantime, the company said it
couldn’t publish annual accounts because of the dispute. Trading
in the company’s shares were suspended by Spain’s market
regulator. The shares fell 3 percent to 16 cents.  Portuguese stocks:  Portugal Telecom SGPS SA (PTC)  : Portugal’s biggest
telephone company is scheduled to report first-quarter earnings
before the market opens. The shares fell 0.2 percent to 8.62
euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
